For those curious about why the Bitcoin price isn't pumping to $100 000 in one go it's important to understand that large institutions (BlackRock) don't buy from the market. They use platforms like Coinbase to make their purchases over-the-counter to minimize price slippage.
The lower the market cap the more opportunities a project has. It is easier for small market caps to get an inflow of a few million making the price go up than it is easy for Bitcoin to 10x in price.
